<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../manrev.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>fr</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>xgraduate  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>November 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="xgraduate"> graduation des axes   </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[xi,xa,np1,np2,kMinr,kMaxr,ar]=xgraduate(xmi,xma)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>xmi,xma  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : scalaire réel
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>xi, xa, kMinr, kMaxr, ar  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    :scalaires réels
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>np1,np2  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  <SP>
    : entier
</SP>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    <VERB>xgraduate</VERB> renvoie les graduations des axes utilisées par les routines de dessin. Elle renvoie un intervalle <VERB>[xi,xa]</VERB> contenant l&apos;intervalle donné <VERB>[xmi,xma]</VERB> avec xi et xa tels que  
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>xi= kMinr*10^ar</VERB>, <VERB>xa=kMaxr*10^ar</VERB> et l&apos;intervalle peut être divise en <VERB>np2</VERB> intervalles et chaque intervalle est divisé en
    <VERB>np1</VERB> sous-intervalles.
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
  [x1,xa,np1,np2,kMinr,kMaxr,ar]=xgraduate(-0.3,0.2)
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
